75 void ScriptMgr::Unload()
76 {
77 #define SCR_CLEAR(T) \
78  for (SCR_REG_ITR(T) itr = SCR_REG_LST(T).begin(); itr != SCR_REG_LST(T).end(); ++itr) \
79  delete itr->second; \
80  SCR_REG_LST(T).clear();
81 
82  // Clear scripts for every script type.
83  SCR_CLEAR(SpellScriptLoader);

157 void ScriptMgr::CheckIfScriptsInDatabaseExist()
158 {
159  for (auto const& scriptName : sObjectMgr->GetScriptNames())
160  {
161  if (uint32 sid = sObjectMgr->GetScriptId(scriptName.c_str()))
162  {
163  if (!ScriptRegistry<SpellScriptLoader>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
164  !ScriptRegistry<ServerScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
165  !ScriptRegistry<WorldScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
166  !ScriptRegistry<FormulaScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
167  !ScriptRegistry<WorldMapScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
168  !ScriptRegistry<InstanceMapScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
169  !ScriptRegistry<BattlegroundMapScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
170  !ScriptRegistry<ItemScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
171  !ScriptRegistry<CreatureScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
172  !ScriptRegistry<GameObjectScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
173  !ScriptRegistry<AreaTriggerScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
174  !ScriptRegistry<BattlegroundScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
175  !ScriptRegistry<OutdoorPvPScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
176  !ScriptRegistry<CommandScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
177  !ScriptRegistry<WeatherScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
178  !ScriptRegistry<AuctionHouseScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
179  !ScriptRegistry<ConditionScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
180  !ScriptRegistry<VehicleScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
181  !ScriptRegistry<DynamicObjectScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
182  !ScriptRegistry<TransportScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
183  !ScriptRegistry<AchievementCriteriaScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
184  !ScriptRegistry<PlayerScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
185  !ScriptRegistry<GuildScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
186  !ScriptRegistry<BGScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
187  !ScriptRegistry<AchievementScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
188  !ScriptRegistry<ArenaTeamScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
189  !ScriptRegistry<SpellSC>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
190  !ScriptRegistry<MiscScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
191  !ScriptRegistry<PetScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
192  !ScriptRegistry<CommandSC>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
193  !ScriptRegistry<ArenaScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
194  !ScriptRegistry<GroupScript>::GetScriptById(sid) &&
195  !ScriptRegistry<DatabaseScript>::GetScriptById(sid))
196  {
197  LOG_ERROR("sql.sql", "Script named '%s' is assigned in the database, but has no code!", scriptName.c_str());
198  }
199  }

203 void ScriptMgr::FillSpellSummary()
204 {
205  UnitAI::FillAISpellInfo();
206 
207  SpellSummary = new TSpellSummary[sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfoStoreSize()];
208 
209  SpellInfo const* pTempSpell;
210 
211  for (uint32 i = 0; i < sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfoStoreSize(); ++i)
212  {
213  SpellSummary[i].Effects = 0;
214  SpellSummary[i].Targets = 0;
215 
216  pTempSpell = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(i);
217  // This spell doesn't exist.
218  if (!pTempSpell)
219  continue;
220 
221  for (uint32 j = 0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
222  {
223  // Spell targets self.
224  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
225  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_SELF - 1);
226 
227  // Spell targets a single enemy.
228  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ENEMY ||
229  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY)
230  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_SINGLE_ENEMY - 1);
231 
232  // Spell targets AoE at enemy.
233  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ENEMY ||
234  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ENEMY ||
235  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER ||
236  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY)
237  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_AOE_ENEMY - 1);
238 
239  // Spell targets an enemy.
240  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ENEMY ||
241  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY ||
242  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ENEMY ||
243  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ENEMY ||
244  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER ||
245  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY)
246  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_ANY_ENEMY - 1);
247 
248  // Spell targets a single friend (or self).
249  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER ||
250  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ALLY ||
251  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_PARTY)
252  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_SINGLE_FRIEND - 1);
253 
254  // Spell targets AoE friends.
255  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER_AREA_PARTY ||
256  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_LASTTARGET_AREA_PARTY ||
257  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER)
258  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_AOE_FRIEND - 1);
259 
260  // Spell targets any friend (or self).
261  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER ||
262  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ALLY ||
263  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_PARTY ||
264  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER_AREA_PARTY ||
265  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_LASTTARGET_AREA_PARTY ||
266  pTempSpell->Effects[j].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_SRC_CASTER)
267  SpellSummary[i].Targets |= 1 << (SELECT_TARGET_ANY_FRIEND - 1);
268 
269  // Make sure that this spell includes a damage effect.
270  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE ||
271  pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_INSTAKILL ||
272  pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_ENVIRONMENTAL_DAMAGE ||
273  pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH)
274  SpellSummary[i].Effects |= 1 << (SELECT_EFFECT_DAMAGE - 1);
275 
276  // Make sure that this spell includes a healing effect (or an apply aura with a periodic heal).
277  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL ||
278  pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_MAX_HEALTH ||
279  pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_MECHANICAL ||
280  (pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA && pTempSpell->Effects[j].ApplyAuraName == 8))
281  SpellSummary[i].Effects |= 1 << (SELECT_EFFECT_HEALING - 1);
282 
283  // Make sure that this spell applies an aura.
284  if (pTempSpell->Effects[j].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
285  SpellSummary[i].Effects |= 1 << (SELECT_EFFECT_AURA - 1);
286  }
287  }
288 }

290 void ScriptMgr::CreateSpellScripts(uint32 spellId, std::list<SpellScript*>& scriptVector)
291 {
292  SpellScriptsBounds bounds = sObjectMgr->GetSpellScriptsBounds(spellId);
293 
294  for (SpellScriptsContainer::iterator itr = bounds.first; itr != bounds.second; ++itr)
295  {
296  SpellScriptLoader* tmpscript = ScriptRegistry<SpellScriptLoader>::GetScriptById(itr->second);
297  if (!tmpscript)
298  continue;
299 
300  SpellScript* script = tmpscript->GetSpellScript();
301 
302  if (!script)
303  continue;
304 
305  script->_Init(&tmpscript->GetName(), spellId);
306 
307  scriptVector.push_back(script);
308  }
309 }

332 void ScriptMgr::CreateSpellScriptLoaders(uint32 spellId, std::vector<std::pair<SpellScriptLoader*, SpellScriptsContainer::iterator> >& scriptVector)
333 {
334  SpellScriptsBounds bounds = sObjectMgr->GetSpellScriptsBounds(spellId);
335  scriptVector.reserve(std::distance(bounds.first, bounds.second));
336 
337  for (SpellScriptsContainer::iterator itr = bounds.first; itr != bounds.second; ++itr)
338  {
339  SpellScriptLoader* tmpscript = ScriptRegistry<SpellScriptLoader>::GetScriptById(itr->second);
340  if (!tmpscript)
341  continue;
342 
343  scriptVector.push_back(std::make_pair(tmpscript, itr));
344  }
345 }

500  FOR_SCRIPTS(M, I, E) \
